[{"id":"VR857475","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows 2 mirrors labeled Mirror X and Mirror Y. The bottom edge of Mirror X is angled tilted to the right at a small angle from the a vertical dashed line. The reflective surface of Mirror X points to the right. Mirror Y is oriented vertically to the right of Mirror X with its reflective surface pointing to the left.  Mirror Y shows a small opening at the center of the mirror. An Initial Ray of light travels from the right and goes through the small opening of Mirror Y and travels towards Mirror X. The angle between the ray of light and Mirror Y is indicated as a right angle. The ray of light makes a right angle with the surface of Mirror Y. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" height=\"278\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857475.g01.svg\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two flat mirrors, Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> are located near each other, as shown in the figure. Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> is oriented at a small but nonnegligible angle from the vertical, as indicated, while Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> is oriented vertically. A light ray travels to the left through a small hole in Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> and is initially perpendicular to Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> as shown. The light ray then has the following interactions with the two mirrors.</p>\n\n<ul class=\"unordered_list style:1\">\n\t<li class=\"list_item\">\n\t<p class=\"list_paragraph\">First, the ray is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> with an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 1, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span> as measured from the normal to the surface of Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>, and is then reflected from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> toward Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_item\">\n\t<p class=\"list_paragraph\">Next, the ray is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> with an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span> as measured from the normal to the surface of Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span>, and is then reflected from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> back toward Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_item\">\n\t<p class=\"list_paragraph\">Finally, the ray is incident on Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> for a second time, with an angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 2, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 2, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span>, and is again reflected from Mirror <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>.</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following correctly ranks the angles of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 1, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 2, end sub\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 2, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857475_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub X 2, end sub, close parenthesis, is greater than theta sub Y 1, end sub\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub X 2, end sub, close parenthesis, is greater than theta sub Y 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 2, end sub, is greater than open parenthesis, theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub Y 1, end sub, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 2, end sub, is greater than open parenthesis, theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub Y 1, end sub, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mpadded><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub X 2, end sub, is greater than theta sub Y 1, end sub, which is greater than theta sub X 1, end sub\"><math alttext=\"theta sub X 2, end sub, is greater than theta sub Y 1, end sub, which is greater than theta sub X 1, end sub\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub, is greater than open parenthesis theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub X 2, end sub, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"theta sub Y 1, end sub, is greater than open parenthesis theta sub X 1, end sub, equals theta sub X 2, end sub, close parenthesis\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mpadded><mo>(</mo><mpadded><mpadded><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mpadded><mo>)</mo></mpadded></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]